1
00:00:00,030 --> 00:00:04,300
Shri Krishna -Virata Puja
“Rise above the Ego to enter Virata’s Kingdom”
September 9, 1999 Cabella, Italia

2
00:00:04,550 --> 00:00:13,609
Tonight we are going to worship Shri Krishna
as Virat.

3
00:00:13,609 --> 00:00:28,309
First is important to understand the incarnation
of Shri Krishna.

4
00:00:28,309 --> 00:00:31,660
Krishna word comes from the word Krishi.

5
00:00:31,660 --> 00:00:33,910
Krishi means agriculture.

6
00:00:33,910 --> 00:00:41,940
He’s sown the seeds of spirituality.

7
00:00:41,940 --> 00:00:52,670
And for that, first of all, He had to think,
“Where are we as far as spirituality is

8
00:00:52,670 --> 00:00:57,590
concerned, how is the land?”

9
00:00:57,590 --> 00:01:08,139
So what had happened at the time of Shri Rama
that He created lots of maryadas and by these

10
00:01:08,139 --> 00:01:13,690
maryadas people started mentally thinking
about it, “I am not supposed to do that,

11
00:01:13,690 --> 00:01:15,630
I am not supposed to do this.”

12
00:01:15,630 --> 00:01:23,610
It was just a mental binding – it was not
spontaneous, it was not sahaj.

13
00:01:23,610 --> 00:01:26,350
As a result people became extremely serious.

14
00:01:26,350 --> 00:01:35,410
They wouldn’t talk much and they wouldn’t
laugh; they wouldn’t enjoy anything.

15
00:01:35,410 --> 00:01:43,919
So Shri Krishna decided that “First of all
we must remove them from this conditioning.

16
00:01:43,919 --> 00:01:57,670
And this conditioning has to be removed in
such a manner that they enjoy themselves.”

17
00:01:57,670 --> 00:02:07,450
Then He found out, there were three suggestions
as far as achieving the goal was concerned.

18
00:02:07,450 --> 00:02:20,540
So first one, as He says, is to become a realized
soul, Sthitapragya, to go beyond all temptations,

19
00:02:20,540 --> 00:02:31,950
go beyond all ego, go beyond all kinds of
conditioning and to become a Sthitapragya.

20
00:02:31,950 --> 00:02:48,920
Sthitapragya is where he doesn’t feel like
ordinary people attracted towards things,

21
00:02:48,920 --> 00:02:54,910
but he’s absolutely detached.

22
00:02:54,910 --> 00:03:09,920
And this detached person doesn’t take to
any grievances, jealousies, all these things.

23
00:03:09,920 --> 00:03:15,050
That He told.

24
00:03:15,050 --> 00:03:20,580
But how to achieve it He never told.

25
00:03:20,580 --> 00:03:24,479
And the second thing He described is that
you must work.

26
00:03:24,479 --> 00:03:25,479
You have to work.

27
00:03:25,479 --> 00:03:33,720
After all, you have got all the human tendencies
– is to work.

28
00:03:33,720 --> 00:03:41,819
But the fruit of the work, you leave it at
the Lotus Feet of God or you may call the

29
00:03:41,819 --> 00:03:45,690
divine Power.

30
00:03:45,690 --> 00:03:52,050
This is another trick of His, because He realized
how human beings were twisted and how they

31
00:03:52,050 --> 00:03:53,050
had a ego.

32
00:03:53,050 --> 00:03:56,000
If you tell them something, how they’ll
misinterpret it.

33
00:03:56,000 --> 00:04:01,220
So He took the other way round, that tell
them something absurd.

34
00:04:01,220 --> 00:04:16,430
Now whatever work you do, your ego is intact
and with that ego, you can never give it up

35
00:04:16,430 --> 00:04:20,980
at the Lotus Feet of the Divine, then impossible.

36
00:04:20,980 --> 00:04:27,770
So He made a impossible situation, that after
some time people will realize that this cannot

37
00:04:27,770 --> 00:04:37,280
be done and they’ll give up this idea of
leaving everything at the Lotus Feet of the

38
00:04:37,280 --> 00:04:38,870
Divine.

39
00:04:38,870 --> 00:04:44,040
This was the one how He prepared the land.

40
00:04:44,040 --> 00:04:50,980
Second thing He said, “Pushpam phalam toyum.

41
00:04:50,980 --> 00:04:58,390
Flowers, fruit and water.

42
00:04:58,390 --> 00:05:00,960
Whatever you offer Me, I will take it.

43
00:05:00,960 --> 00:05:03,740
I’ll take it.”

44
00:05:03,740 --> 00:05:10,920
But when you do that, when you do that you
must have ananya bhakti.

45
00:05:10,920 --> 00:05:24,970
Ananya means completely single-minded bhakti,
when there is not the other.

46
00:05:24,970 --> 00:05:29,810
This is only possible after realization.

47
00:05:29,810 --> 00:05:38,780
Only after realization you can put the fruits
of your work at the Lotus Feet of the Divine.

48
00:05:38,780 --> 00:05:47,060
And only after Self-realization you can have
ananya bhakti – means the devotion which

49
00:05:47,060 --> 00:05:51,960
is singular.

50
00:05:51,960 --> 00:05:59,000
These absurd conditions He put for human beings
because they were so much complicated.

51
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:03,420
So many people tell Me, “Mother we are doing
ananya bhakti.”

52
00:06:03,420 --> 00:06:04,420
“How?”

53
00:06:04,420 --> 00:06:09,130
“Because we are singing on the street, we
are taking the name of God all the time.

54
00:06:09,130 --> 00:06:19,190
We are going to Pandharipur, you see, in rags
and for one month we walk singing, singing,

55
00:06:19,190 --> 00:06:20,190
singing.”

56
00:06:20,190 --> 00:06:27,690
This kind of absurd ideas about bhakti, He
never gave.

57
00:06:27,690 --> 00:06:36,380
But it is the way He wanted to neutralize
the absurdities of human beings, that they

58
00:06:36,380 --> 00:06:38,770
thought this was the bhakti.

59
00:06:38,770 --> 00:06:40,200
Which is not.

60
00:06:40,200 --> 00:06:45,810
Ananya bhakti is only possible when you are
realized soul, when you are connected with

61
00:06:45,810 --> 00:06:51,010
the Divine, when there’s not the other.

62
00:06:51,010 --> 00:07:00,240
This is how He tried to make three-way attack
I should (say), on human beings, in a way,

63
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:01,870
on their stupidity.

64
00:07:01,870 --> 00:07:07,620
Because He thought that “If I tell them
directly do like this, do like that, then

65
00:07:07,620 --> 00:07:12,950
they’ll say, ‘Of course we did it, and
still we never achieved it.’”

66
00:07:12,950 --> 00:07:21,290
In India there’s a big cult, we can call
it – people who go to Pandharipur.

67
00:07:21,290 --> 00:07:28,700
For one month they walk in rags, singing the
songs and on the way they go on eating food

68
00:07:28,700 --> 00:07:30,930
at different places.

69
00:07:30,930 --> 00:07:35,660
According to them this is ananya bhakti, and
they achieve nothing.

70
00:07:35,660 --> 00:07:44,960
They have become very sick and very tired
and have a very bad old age.

71
00:07:44,960 --> 00:07:47,250
But who can tell them?

72
00:07:47,250 --> 00:07:49,710
They are all lost in it.

73
00:07:49,710 --> 00:07:59,610
So this is a way one could tackle human beings
to show their stupidity.

74
00:07:59,610 --> 00:08:05,560
And so many people come and ask Me, as I told
you, that “How is it we do so much bhakti

75
00:08:05,560 --> 00:08:10,990
of Shri Krishna and we have achieved nothing?”

76
00:08:10,990 --> 00:08:15,160
So He’s the One who prepared the land for
sowing.

77
00:08:15,160 --> 00:08:23,840
We can say He’s the One who was like a very
great agriculturist.

78
00:08:23,840 --> 00:08:25,770
So His name was Krishi – Krishna.

79
00:08:25,770 --> 00:08:32,530
There are so many things I have told you about
Him: how His name came as Krishna, then as

80
00:08:32,530 --> 00:08:41,550
how He was called as Radha, who was Radha,
who was Krishna and all those things.

81
00:08:41,550 --> 00:08:50,290
But when He talked of these things also He
told that you should become Sthitapragya.

82
00:08:50,290 --> 00:08:52,560
That is they call as Gyana Yoga.

83
00:08:52,560 --> 00:08:54,880
Gyana means knowledge.

84
00:08:54,880 --> 00:08:58,870
So, you should get absolute knowledge.

85
00:08:58,870 --> 00:09:00,880
That He didn’t say how.

86
00:09:00,880 --> 00:09:05,280
That you know, what is absolute knowledge,
which you can feel it on your finger tips

87
00:09:05,280 --> 00:09:11,480
in Sahaja Yoga.

88
00:09:11,480 --> 00:09:17,460
Another thing is, His specialty was to create
discretion in people.

89
00:09:17,460 --> 00:09:24,020
He thought by doing all these things in a
stupid manner, they might develop a discretion

90
00:09:24,020 --> 00:09:27,670
to know that this is not the way you can achieve
anything.

91
00:09:27,670 --> 00:09:30,030
You have to get your Self-realization.

92
00:09:30,030 --> 00:09:33,210
Discretion was very important.

93
00:09:33,210 --> 00:09:45,740
At this juncture, when we are facing a sort
of a challenge of this new millennium – that

94
00:09:45,740 --> 00:09:50,880
the whole world is going to be destroyed and
all those things people are talking – it

95
00:09:50,880 --> 00:10:02,380
is really very important to know through discretion
what is good and what is bad.

96
00:10:02,380 --> 00:10:08,420
One may talk of something as very good, something
as very bad.

97
00:10:08,420 --> 00:10:13,382
But the divine Discretion is very, very different.

98
00:10:13,382 --> 00:10:17,480
Very different and which acts by Itself.

99
00:10:17,480 --> 00:10:23,780
Once you are in the realm of divine Discretion
you cannot commit mistakes – even if you

100
00:10:23,780 --> 00:10:24,780
want to do it.

101
00:10:24,780 --> 00:10:27,350
I’ll give you My example.

102
00:10:27,350 --> 00:10:36,980
We went to buy a house and the fellow was,
you see, like a beggar he came.

103
00:10:36,980 --> 00:10:38,770
He said, “We have nothing.

104
00:10:38,770 --> 00:10:40,310
We have no food.

105
00:10:40,310 --> 00:10:45,450
They have taken away all our things and we
are just absolutely starving.”

106
00:10:45,450 --> 00:10:57,150
When they said that, when he said that “We
are starving, we have nothing,” so I felt

107
00:10:57,150 --> 00:10:58,150
pity for him.

108
00:10:58,150 --> 00:11:00,050
I said, “All right, increase the price.”

109
00:11:00,050 --> 00:11:02,190
First we increased the price.

110
00:11:02,190 --> 00:11:05,560
Still he was saying, “No, no give us more.”

111
00:11:05,560 --> 00:11:07,240
Still we increased the price.

112
00:11:07,240 --> 00:11:09,590
I told My husband, “You increase the price.”

113
00:11:09,590 --> 00:11:12,910
Though reluctantly, he increased the price.

114
00:11:12,910 --> 00:11:15,560
Third time again we increased the price.

115
00:11:15,560 --> 00:11:20,510
Then he said, “No, we’ll have something
more than that, a little more.”

116
00:11:20,510 --> 00:11:27,100
Immediately you see, this Discretion worked
and I said, “These are hypocrites.”

117
00:11:27,100 --> 00:11:32,120
I just left them and sat in the car – at
the right moment.

118
00:11:32,120 --> 00:11:36,660
That was not such a good proposition or anything.

119
00:11:36,660 --> 00:11:43,570
But I could see they, I’m buying it out
of My pity; you may call it compassion.

120
00:11:43,570 --> 00:11:49,900
But above the compassion was this Discretion,
which said, “Nothing doing, You better get

121
00:11:49,900 --> 00:11:51,370
out of it.”

122
00:11:51,370 --> 00:11:58,080
So this divine Discretion is a very, very
important thing, which we should see how it

123
00:11:58,080 --> 00:12:02,530
works and should be satisfied with it.

124
00:12:02,530 --> 00:12:08,640
Not to feel bad, that you have missed a chance
or anything, but you must feel very happy

125
00:12:08,640 --> 00:12:16,220
that this thing has happened and that your
divine discretion has taken on.

126
00:12:16,220 --> 00:12:23,230
So sometimes it appears that, in that divine
discretion you may do something wrong, you

127
00:12:23,230 --> 00:12:24,230
have done something wrong.

128
00:12:24,230 --> 00:12:29,870
But if it is divine, ultimately it will turn
out to be very good.

129
00:12:29,870 --> 00:12:34,850
I gave you a very basic example.

130
00:12:34,850 --> 00:12:43,670
But that is also very true when you practice
Sahaja Yoga.

131
00:12:43,670 --> 00:12:53,280
The discretion of divine Discretion is extremely
important to play a very great part in our

132
00:12:53,280 --> 00:13:02,700
lives, because this divine Discretion gives
us the real joy of our being, of our self,

133
00:13:02,700 --> 00:13:05,730
of Sahaja Yoga.

134
00:13:05,730 --> 00:13:13,140
So the third point was for Him to make people
joyous and happy.

135
00:13:13,140 --> 00:13:20,650
But with all these maryadas of Shri Rama,
He didn’t know how to do it.

136
00:13:20,650 --> 00:13:28,499
So to give people joy He said, “All right,
let us dance, let us sing, let us play Holi,

137
00:13:28,499 --> 00:13:37,010
all sorts of things,” and with that He really
originated many things which were sort of

138
00:13:37,010 --> 00:13:38,880
not serious.

139
00:13:38,880 --> 00:13:43,140
May look frivolous, but in that there was
joy expressing.

140
00:13:43,140 --> 00:13:52,831
All that He did to give them a full idea as
for a Sahaja yogi or for a, you can say, for

141
00:13:52,831 --> 00:13:59,500
a self realized soul, what should be the attitude
towards everything.

142
00:13:59,500 --> 00:14:08,910
But it is not that you have to do it, but
it just works out, it is like that, that in

143
00:14:08,910 --> 00:14:13,680
the state of Sahaj, you enjoy everything.

144
00:14:13,680 --> 00:14:15,680
Enjoyment.

145
00:14:15,680 --> 00:14:23,560
And that is what His idea was, to create a
sense of joy among people.

146
00:14:23,560 --> 00:14:28,470
Many people – there are lots of critics
– have criticized this part of His life.

147
00:14:28,470 --> 00:14:32,370
According to them, religion means you should
become just old.

148
00:14:32,370 --> 00:14:38,360
At the age of twenty years you should become
an old man of eighty years – something like

149
00:14:38,360 --> 00:14:43,300
that, funny ideas of religious achievement.

150
00:14:43,300 --> 00:14:49,170
But He talked of joy and He never talked of
renunciation.

151
00:14:49,170 --> 00:14:57,660
He never talked that “You give up your family,
you give up your children, you give up everything,”

152
00:14:57,660 --> 00:14:59,120
never, never.

153
00:14:59,120 --> 00:15:04,220
He said, “You must enjoy, enjoy with detachment.”

154
00:15:04,220 --> 00:15:09,640
For people it is very difficult to understand
how can it be it is without detachment.

155
00:15:09,640 --> 00:15:13,460
With attachment you can never enjoy.

156
00:15:13,460 --> 00:15:19,870
If you are attached to something, you cannot
enjoy anything in a full way.

157
00:15:19,870 --> 00:15:22,999
Like, supposing you are attached to your child.

158
00:15:22,999 --> 00:15:25,940
Very simple thing, you are attached to your
child.

159
00:15:25,940 --> 00:15:31,680
You’re attached to your child, then you
will be bothered about things which should

160
00:15:31,680 --> 00:15:35,430
not be there, which will not give joy to the
child either.

161
00:15:35,430 --> 00:15:42,810
You’ll not allow your child, say, to go
out or to talk to people, whatever it is – all

162
00:15:42,810 --> 00:15:45,650
kinds of restrictions you will put.

163
00:15:45,650 --> 00:15:54,290
But if you have really the divine discretion,
then you will know with whom he should talk,

164
00:15:54,290 --> 00:16:02,830
where he should go, what he should enjoy and
you will see that he enjoys life.

165
00:16:02,830 --> 00:16:11,110
Any attachment with anything doesn’t give
you the full view of that person, of that

166
00:16:11,110 --> 00:16:12,840
thing.

167
00:16:12,840 --> 00:16:22,870
If you are detached, then you can see it,
say, from above … above him, above the thing.

168
00:16:22,870 --> 00:16:27,140
If you are detached, you become thoughtlessly
aware, also.

169
00:16:27,140 --> 00:16:30,730
As I said, now, see the carpets are there.

170
00:16:30,730 --> 00:16:34,110
They are very, very beautiful carpets.

171
00:16:34,110 --> 00:16:40,070
Now if they are here, if they are Mine, I’ll
be worried, I’ll be all the time worried

172
00:16:40,070 --> 00:16:47,340
because I am attached – that these carpets
should not be spoilt, something will go wrong.

173
00:16:47,340 --> 00:16:51,640
But if I’m not attached, I’ll look at
those carpets and what do I see?

174
00:16:51,640 --> 00:16:52,900
The joy.

175
00:16:52,900 --> 00:16:58,140
The joy that is put in by the artist who has
made them.

176
00:16:58,140 --> 00:17:06,410
And that joy really tries to reflect in Me
also.

177
00:17:06,410 --> 00:17:09,369
That joy comes in Me.

178
00:17:09,369 --> 00:17:18,750
So to have anything, attachment to anything,
there will be joy … I should say there’ll

179
00:17:18,750 --> 00:17:22,310
be happiness but not joy.

180
00:17:22,310 --> 00:17:30,990
Because joy is single and happiness is double
– happiness and unhappiness.

181
00:17:30,990 --> 00:17:35,790
So even if I try to enjoy something, I’ll
think, “Oh, still there, this, this point

182
00:17:35,790 --> 00:17:37,430
is there.”

183
00:17:37,430 --> 00:17:40,390
But joy is all pervading.

184
00:17:40,390 --> 00:17:43,890
It has no boundaries.

185
00:17:43,890 --> 00:17:48,880
And you just get dissolved, you get dissolved
in the ocean of joy.

186
00:17:48,880 --> 00:17:56,540
That was what Shri Krishna’s idea was, that
cut out these maryadas.

187
00:17:56,540 --> 00:18:02,690
Nowadays we see the maryadas of so many things
are really useless.

188
00:18:02,690 --> 00:18:08,000
For example, you have discovered the maryadas
of religion.

189
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:12,170
See when they live in maryadas then what happens?

190
00:18:12,170 --> 00:18:23,719
They sort of coggle it or they have all kinds
of germination inside like the pond, which

191
00:18:23,719 --> 00:18:29,540
is absolutely bound, it is not flowing like
river.

192
00:18:29,540 --> 00:18:40,770
So like that, you see, it becomes a kind of
a closed mind with these maryadas.

193
00:18:40,770 --> 00:18:48,100
And when you have this maryadas, you start
thinking, “Whether I should do it or not;

194
00:18:48,100 --> 00:18:50,790
whether I’ll enjoy it or not.”

195
00:18:50,790 --> 00:18:55,740
With these maryadas only, you kill the joy.

196
00:18:55,740 --> 00:19:01,840
Now we have other maryadas about, say, we
have country … as I said about the religion.

197
00:19:01,840 --> 00:19:08,710
Now many people who love to come to Sahaj
Yoga, but because they have maryadas of silly

198
00:19:08,710 --> 00:19:12,860
things of their religion, they cannot come.

199
00:19:12,860 --> 00:19:16,740
They think, “This is our religion,” while
they don’t understand.

200
00:19:16,740 --> 00:19:24,140
Falsehood becomes the maryadas and they don’t
understand that what is the maryada actually

201
00:19:24,140 --> 00:19:27,250
made by the religion also.

202
00:19:27,250 --> 00:19:29,810
You see now in Islam what is happening is.

203
00:19:29,810 --> 00:19:38,120
With these maryadas, they want to have another
country, this thing, that thing.

204
00:19:38,120 --> 00:19:41,580
In other Christian religion also same thing
happening.

205
00:19:41,580 --> 00:19:43,240
Also in Hindu religion.

206
00:19:43,240 --> 00:19:49,969
All these maryadas are really stagnating them
completely, and they are getting crushed into

207
00:19:49,969 --> 00:19:51,089
it.

208
00:19:51,089 --> 00:19:54,450
There’s no discretion.

209
00:19:54,450 --> 00:19:58,130
Because they have said it, they do it.

210
00:19:58,130 --> 00:20:04,820
They are so much blind-folded about it, that
they cannot see what is right and what is

211
00:20:04,820 --> 00:20:05,820
wrong.

212
00:20:05,820 --> 00:20:11,510
But after Sahaj, you can see, you can laugh
at them and you can see.

213
00:20:11,510 --> 00:20:16,880
Then we have social maryadas.

214
00:20:16,880 --> 00:20:23,990
Social maryadas are there which are sometimes,
when abandoned can become very horrid also.

215
00:20:23,990 --> 00:20:31,320
Like in the West now, the women think that
the less dress they wear, the more beautiful

216
00:20:31,320 --> 00:20:32,320
they are.

217
00:20:32,320 --> 00:20:34,690
This is a new thing they have started.

218
00:20:34,690 --> 00:20:36,790
Now this absurd.

219
00:20:36,790 --> 00:20:44,300
If you see the discretion behind is very simple:
that we have been animals and now we don’t

220
00:20:44,300 --> 00:20:49,860
want to have any clothes because we were animals.

221
00:20:49,860 --> 00:20:56,260
Is a animal heritage that if … that’s
why so many women do not want to wear full

222
00:20:56,260 --> 00:20:57,260
dresses.

223
00:20:57,260 --> 00:20:59,900
It’s just animal behavior.

224
00:20:59,900 --> 00:21:06,830
So the maryada of – good maryadas also people
can give up saying that “We don’t want

225
00:21:06,830 --> 00:21:07,830
any maryadas.

226
00:21:07,830 --> 00:21:10,400
We are free; we can do whatever we like.”

227
00:21:10,400 --> 00:21:14,970
But in that freedom what do you achieve?

228
00:21:14,970 --> 00:21:22,280
Your animal instinct works in that freedom
and you think you are a very free personality.

229
00:21:22,280 --> 00:21:24,930
Then we have maryadas of our country.

230
00:21:24,930 --> 00:21:28,870
God has not made different, different countries
at all.

231
00:21:28,870 --> 00:21:33,450
Nor it is true there are different countries,
but variety is there.

232
00:21:33,450 --> 00:21:37,670
Variety of people, variety of places is there.

233
00:21:37,670 --> 00:21:45,910
These varieties must be accepted as something
very artistic and one should not get ruined

234
00:21:45,910 --> 00:21:52,980
and confused with those ideas that “We are
Americans, we are Indians, we are this and

235
00:21:52,980 --> 00:21:54,140
we are that.”

236
00:21:54,140 --> 00:21:55,140
You’re not.

237
00:21:55,140 --> 00:22:00,600
Now you can know after Sahaja Yoga, that you
are all Sahaja yogis and you don’t belong

238
00:22:00,600 --> 00:22:02,839
to any country as such.

239
00:22:02,839 --> 00:22:06,209
The country may belong to you, but you don’t
belong to the country.

240
00:22:06,209 --> 00:22:14,730
I mean the work is today to understand that
if you really want to care for all these countries

241
00:22:14,730 --> 00:22:23,100
and all that, then you must do some work – work
of Sahaja Yoga so that people get rid of these

242
00:22:23,100 --> 00:22:28,790
silly ideas of fighting for territory, for
this, for that.

243
00:22:28,790 --> 00:22:34,380
All over the world there’s going on, “We
want this land; we want that land.”

244
00:22:34,380 --> 00:22:38,060
Land belongs to God, not to human beings.

245
00:22:38,060 --> 00:22:40,589
And what is the use of fighting for land?

246
00:22:40,589 --> 00:22:42,380
I don’t understand.

247
00:22:42,380 --> 00:22:45,460
But this confusion is there and illusion is
there.

248
00:22:45,460 --> 00:22:50,800
And people work out on this confusion and
illusion to such an extent that they ruin

249
00:22:50,800 --> 00:22:53,280
their lives, the lives of their children.

250
00:22:53,280 --> 00:23:01,280
So many people are lost, so many people are
in the lunatic asylum, I should say, because

251
00:23:01,280 --> 00:23:05,200
they end up in some sort of a refugee camp.

252
00:23:05,200 --> 00:23:09,690
They are having a good house, nicely living
there.

253
00:23:09,690 --> 00:23:12,010
Then you become a refugee.

254
00:23:12,010 --> 00:23:13,510
Why?

255
00:23:13,510 --> 00:23:21,590
Because they believe that they can have their
own land, they can have their own place and

256
00:23:21,590 --> 00:23:23,680
they should live there.

257
00:23:23,680 --> 00:23:30,230
This idea comes, I think, from some stupid
leaders who want to have for themselves these

258
00:23:30,230 --> 00:23:33,570
lands and that’s how people fight for land.

259
00:23:33,570 --> 00:23:40,671
There’s no need to fight for land or fight
for your country or fight for this or fight

260
00:23:40,671 --> 00:23:41,940
for that.

261
00:23:41,940 --> 00:23:49,089
But the situation is such that unless and
until you fight, you cannot get to the truth.

262
00:23:49,089 --> 00:23:56,670
And that’s why if you remember that Shri
Krishna told Arjuna that “You fight.

263
00:23:56,670 --> 00:23:57,670
Fight.

264
00:23:57,670 --> 00:23:59,719
You have to fight, that’s your work.

265
00:23:59,719 --> 00:24:05,740
You have to fight these people, because they
are the people who do not live with dharma.

266
00:24:05,740 --> 00:24:09,760
They are adharmis, so you have to fight.”

267
00:24:09,760 --> 00:24:17,969
And that is how his fighting was so much justified,
because after fighting the war they got back

268
00:24:17,969 --> 00:24:19,740
what they deserved.

269
00:24:19,740 --> 00:24:27,740
They were deceived, and this is what Shri
Krishna said that “You should not by any

270
00:24:27,740 --> 00:24:37,170
chance become a slave of these people, but
you fight it back.”

271
00:24:37,170 --> 00:24:42,270
So fighting also is justified in the divine
discretion.

272
00:24:42,270 --> 00:24:48,089
Is again the divine discretion where you have
to fight because you don’t want to be a

273
00:24:48,089 --> 00:24:49,140
slave.

274
00:24:49,140 --> 00:24:51,589
If you are a slave, you are no good.

275
00:24:51,589 --> 00:24:53,500
So for that you can fight.

276
00:24:53,500 --> 00:25:01,780
But when people start fighting for separation
of a territory, is not correct.

277
00:25:01,780 --> 00:25:06,860
On the contrary, one should never think of
separating from the main lands.

278
00:25:06,860 --> 00:25:10,839
Because it creates lots of problems.

279
00:25:10,839 --> 00:25:14,630
But now we believe in the global religion.

280
00:25:14,630 --> 00:25:17,450
We believe in the global territory.

281
00:25:17,450 --> 00:25:19,770
We don’t have to ask for anything.

282
00:25:19,770 --> 00:25:23,350
Anywhere you go, you are the citizen of that
place.

283
00:25:23,350 --> 00:25:28,900
Anybody who wants to go to Russia ever, the
whole Russians will be with you.

284
00:25:28,900 --> 00:25:31,880
You go to America, they’ll be with you.

285
00:25:31,880 --> 00:25:37,730
That’s how because all these are ideas of
human beings, and if the human beings get

286
00:25:37,730 --> 00:25:46,130
transformed there will be no problem of any
war or any territory to be achieved.

287
00:25:46,130 --> 00:25:53,620
This was the divine Discretion of Shri Krishna,
which is instilled within us.

288
00:25:53,620 --> 00:26:04,380
As you know that this is a part and parcel
of the Vishuddhi Chakra, where Shri Krishna

289
00:26:04,380 --> 00:26:14,400
resides; but when He rises to your Sahasrara,
when He rises to that level, then He becomes

290
00:26:14,400 --> 00:26:17,330
Virata.

291
00:26:17,330 --> 00:26:30,440
So Virata’s Chakra is placed in the head,
here above the Agnya, and this Virat is the

292
00:26:30,440 --> 00:26:37,790
form of Shri Krishna who has risen above the
Agnya.

293
00:26:37,790 --> 00:26:46,730
When you are risen above the Agnya, you become
a part and parcel of Virata’s land, we can

294
00:26:46,730 --> 00:26:48,140
say.

295
00:26:48,140 --> 00:26:56,860
Because, unless and until you are above your
ego, you are still involved with yourself

296
00:26:56,860 --> 00:27:00,630
and with wrong ideas of maryadas.

297
00:27:00,630 --> 00:27:07,640
But when you rise above that and you become
the Virat, the great, then you are in the

298
00:27:07,640 --> 00:27:10,070
land of Virata.

299
00:27:10,070 --> 00:27:13,110
And Virata’s powers are tremendous.

300
00:27:13,110 --> 00:27:17,510
Has been seen by Arjuna – the form of Virat.

301
00:27:17,510 --> 00:27:24,410
The power of Virat becomes so tremendous that
it acts globally.

302
00:27:24,410 --> 00:27:37,390
It acts in such a manner that you sit here
and anywhere it can act.

303
00:27:37,390 --> 00:27:38,430
You have seen that now.

304
00:27:38,430 --> 00:27:42,390
Many a times people say, “Mother it’s
a miracle.

305
00:27:42,390 --> 00:27:49,959
My mother was sick and she was not here and
I just prayed and she got all right.”

306
00:27:49,959 --> 00:27:53,930
This is all the power of Virat.

307
00:27:53,930 --> 00:28:02,510
The power of Virata is that it can penetrate
into the subtle side of human beings in such

308
00:28:02,510 --> 00:28:06,440
a manner that everything we are connected
with.

309
00:28:06,440 --> 00:28:09,130
We are not separate.

310
00:28:09,130 --> 00:28:11,560
And every drop is connected with the ocean.

311
00:28:11,560 --> 00:28:15,610
We are connected with the whole universe.

312
00:28:15,610 --> 00:28:27,381
And when you become a citizens, I should say,
of Virat, then all the things with which you

313
00:28:27,381 --> 00:28:38,910
are connected also get your vibrations, your
ideas, your ambitions.

314
00:28:38,910 --> 00:28:44,250
Everything passes through that and it works
– it works.

315
00:28:44,250 --> 00:28:49,250
You have seen how many miracles have taken
place in your lives.

316
00:28:49,250 --> 00:28:53,160
It is the Virata Shakti that works.

317
00:28:53,160 --> 00:29:02,850
Now for that we have to know how to do worship
of Virata.

318
00:29:02,850 --> 00:29:10,920
First of all you have to rise above your ego
– very important.

319
00:29:10,920 --> 00:29:13,959
Otherwise how can you worship?

320
00:29:13,959 --> 00:29:24,339
There is your ego standing in between and
how can you rise up to the point of Virat?

321
00:29:24,339 --> 00:29:27,560
You have to pass through that.

322
00:29:27,560 --> 00:29:35,350
Once you are above your ego, you enter into
the kingdom of Virata.

323
00:29:35,350 --> 00:29:44,790
There the King is the Virat and you are the
subject who are looked after completely by

324
00:29:44,790 --> 00:29:48,400
Virata Shakti, by the power of Virata.

325
00:29:48,400 --> 00:29:55,630
But at that stage you become really a universal
personality, in a way, because whatever are

326
00:29:55,630 --> 00:30:03,060
problems universally – now not necessarily
that they should be attached to you or connected

327
00:30:03,060 --> 00:30:04,930
to you.

328
00:30:04,930 --> 00:30:07,260
Supposing a person is of that level.

329
00:30:07,260 --> 00:30:15,400
Now there may be a war in some other country
– it can stop.

330
00:30:15,400 --> 00:30:20,530
Somebody who is being oppressed can win over.

331
00:30:20,530 --> 00:30:23,720
Anywhere your compassion moves it works out.

332
00:30:23,720 --> 00:30:27,320
Whenever your attention will go, it will work
out.

333
00:30:27,320 --> 00:30:32,210
And sometimes you are surprised as to how
it works, “Mother, how these things work

334
00:30:32,210 --> 00:30:33,210
out?

335
00:30:33,210 --> 00:30:37,980
How coincidences … how these coincidences
have taken place?”

336
00:30:37,980 --> 00:30:46,000
Only thing is you have crossed that state
of your ego and have gone into the state of

337
00:30:46,000 --> 00:30:54,709
Virat, which is a very important thing to
do – is to enter into the area of Virata.

338
00:30:54,709 --> 00:30:57,079
Then you don’t think, “This is your country.

339
00:30:57,079 --> 00:30:59,459
This belongs to you, that belongs to you.”

340
00:30:59,459 --> 00:31:02,290
This belonging business finishes off.

341
00:31:02,290 --> 00:31:04,560
Then you belong to Virat.

342
00:31:04,560 --> 00:31:12,910
And He uses you for His own purpose in the
sense that when your whole thinking is different

343
00:31:12,910 --> 00:31:18,250
– becomes global thinking, then He acts.

344
00:31:18,250 --> 00:31:20,630
And then His powers are many-fold.

345
00:31:20,630 --> 00:31:28,079
And Krishna’s power is that He uses a conch
to call people.

346
00:31:28,079 --> 00:31:31,459
I have given conches to all the leaders.

347
00:31:31,459 --> 00:31:37,130
So we have to now announce and call people.

348
00:31:37,130 --> 00:31:45,079
But at the level of Virat, you don’t have
to do all that.

349
00:31:45,079 --> 00:31:53,220
At the level of Virat it just – people see,
they’ll know.

350
00:31:53,220 --> 00:31:58,250
Just they will watch you and they will know.

351
00:31:58,250 --> 00:32:05,150
Just they will think you are human beings
and you are so sweet, so good, just like gems

352
00:32:05,150 --> 00:32:06,710
shining all the time.

353
00:32:06,710 --> 00:32:09,940
So, they’ll be impressed.

354
00:32:09,940 --> 00:32:12,380
This comes through the Virata’s blessing.

355
00:32:12,380 --> 00:32:20,660
When you become that, then you forget about
other things like you have big positions or

356
00:32:20,660 --> 00:32:27,740
anything, you come from a very rich family
or that – all these nonsensical things which

357
00:32:27,740 --> 00:32:30,250
are actually not true.

358
00:32:30,250 --> 00:32:36,839
And all these things on which you want to
exist are no more.

359
00:32:36,839 --> 00:32:47,300
People like to show off their wealth, some
people like to be very sort of demonstrative

360
00:32:47,300 --> 00:32:52,690
of what they think they are.

361
00:32:52,690 --> 00:33:01,060
But in the case of a person who rises above
his ego, and he’s a part and parcel of that

362
00:33:01,060 --> 00:33:08,100
Virata shakti, enters into the kingdom of
Virata, he knows he is very small.

363
00:33:08,100 --> 00:33:15,640
He is very small compared to that and he just
dissolves into that Shakti.

364
00:33:15,640 --> 00:33:19,219
And this should happen to us that we should
humble down.

365
00:33:19,219 --> 00:33:29,441
We should humble down and know that our powers,
whatever we have, if they give us ego, we

366
00:33:29,441 --> 00:33:31,260
should get rid of it.

367
00:33:31,260 --> 00:33:33,260
We should not have that ego.

368
00:33:33,260 --> 00:33:41,390
We should get rid of it and we should actually
achieve that state where you can be called

369
00:33:41,390 --> 00:33:43,640
as citizens of the Virata’s Power.

370
00:33:47,450 --> 00:33:49,160
May God bless you all.

371
00:35:53,236 --> 00:35:56,835
Now when you are entering into the kingdom
of Virata, you have to be like children.

372
00:35:57,706 --> 00:35:59,656
You are children there.

373
00:36:00,206 --> 00:36:02,146
As children you enter.

374
00:36:02,516 --> 00:36:12,966
As Christ has said, “When you enter into
the Kingdom of God you have to be like children.”

375
00:36:13,006 --> 00:36:19,356
And that’s what you have to be today, all
of you to be innocent like children.

376
00:36:19,406 --> 00:36:22,336
You have to be innocent like children.

